(1711, 6, '2015-03-10 21:40:18', '2015-03-10 13:40:18', '<p style="text-align: left;"><img class=" size-full wp-image-1712 alignnone" src="http://devtradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Screen-Shot-2015-03-10-at-9.05.41-pm.png" alt="TradeHero on CNBC" width="563" height="313" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">You might have seen this on our <a title="TradeHero Facebook " href="https://www.facebook.com/TradeHero" target="_blank">Facebook page</a>, but we''re so proud we had to post twice. Our CEO and Co-Founder Dinesh Bhatia was featured in an interview for <a href="http://video.cnbc.com/gallery/?video=3000359661">CNBC</a> this week!</p> <BR>\nWe were invited to the show to talk about TradeHero''s recent success, including adding 400,000 users every month in China, receiving over 8000 reviews on the app stores,  and remaining the Number 1 finance app in 91 countries.\n\nCNBC asked us "Are there real benefits from playing the game?" - Of course! Our app brings Gamification to the finance world, creating a fun learning experience for our users. How much risk would you be willing to take in the stock market, if you were a beginner?? Instead of taking a blind leap of faith and investing your hard earned money, we give players the chance to test their skills and learn from the live market within the game. It''s education, and here''s an amazing fact from us:\n\n<BR><BR>\n\n<img class=" size-full wp-image-1713 alignnone" src="http://devtradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Screen-Shot-2015-03-10-at-9.06.04-pm.png" alt="TradeHero on CNBC 2" width="561" height="313" />\n\n<BR><BR>\n\nIn 2014, <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/sg/app/tradehero-mobile/id572226383?mt=8">TradeHero App</a> top traders actually BEAT the S&amp;P 500 by 3X! Summed up simply? Some of our traders are as good as, if not - BETTER than the real live traders running around Wall Street.\n\nThis fact got CNBC asking us: "Can I, the user make real money from this app?" - The answer is YES. By being a social investment game app, TradeHero allows users to follow other expert investors for a token fee to mirror their trade activity. We give these expert users their fair share of the pie, meaning they make real money $$. So fancy yourself an expert on TradeHero? You could potentially make a good amount of money from it!\n<BR><BR>\nLastly, CNBC asked us: "By playing the game, could I get a job?" - And we''re confident to say this: You''ll become an expert on the stock market by playing TradeHero, and when you take those skills into real cash investments, you''ll be making enough money to not even need a job :)\n\nFor those who haven''t tried TradeHero yet - Give it a shot!<BR><BR>\n<ul>\n	<li>iTunes: https://itunes.apple.com/sg/app/tradehero-mobile/id572226383?mt=8</li>\n	<li>Google Play: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.tradehero.th&amp;hl=en</li><BR><BR>\n</ul>\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1714" src="http://devtradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Screen-Shot-2015-03-10-at-9.06.24-pm.png" alt="CNBC interview with Dinesh Bhatia''s" width="565" height="317" />', 'TradeHero app is a ''Stock trading Monopoly'' - Featured on CNBC', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tradehero-app-is-a-stock-trading-monopoly-featured-on-cnbc', '', '', '2015-03-10 21:40:18', '2015-03-10 13:40:18', '', 0, 'http://en.tradehero.mobi/?p=1711', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1828, 6, '2015-04-01 18:22:06', '2015-04-01 10:22:06', '<a href="http://http://en.tradehero.mobi/sgxstockwhiz2015"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1829 " src="http://devtradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/StockWhiz-banner_revised.jpg" alt="SGX StockWhiz 2015" width="720" height="363" /></a>\n<br><br>\nTraders! We have some fantastic news for you and a reason to put all your investing know-how to test this April. We’ve teamed up with the <a href="http://www.sgx.com/">Singapore Exchange (SGX)</a> to offer an exclusive, one-of-a-kind virtual investing competition – StockWhiz 2015\n<br><br>\nWhy? We want you to you to compete with regional traders, hone your investing acumen and get rewarded generously for your efforts.\n<br><br>\n<strong>What’s up with the PRIZES?\n</strong>We have LOADS of prizes for those who enter the TradeHero battlefield besides the pride of getting on the leaderboard and winning the adoration of all your TradeHero followers.\n<br><br>\n<strong>They include:\n</strong><span style="line-height: 1.5;"><br>- 2x Samsung Galaxy S5\n</span><br>- S$200,000 worth of <a href="http://portal.iocbc.com/help-and-support/Terms_Conditions.html#StockWhiz2015">OCBC Securities (OSPL)Commission Credits</a> you can use for REAL trades.\n<br>- S$21,000 in Cash Prizes\n<br><br>\nDo you have what it takes to get onto the leaderboard?\nStockWhiz 2015 starts 1st April, and ends on the 30th June, giving you plenty of time to buy, hold, sell, and reap those returns as a TradeHero. So what are you waiting for? Download the <a href="http://smarturl.it/tradehero">TradeHero app</a> and join the SGX StockWhiz 2015 now!\n<br><br>\nFor details please check out: <a href="http://en.tradehero.mobi/sgxstockwhiz2015">http://en.tradehero.mobi/sgxstockwhiz2015</a>', '"TradeHero launches the SGX StockWhiz 2015 in partnership with Singapore Exchange! More than $200,000 worth of prizes and 2 Samsung Galaxy S5 to be won!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tradehero-launches-the-sgx-stockwhiz-2015-in-partnership-with-singapore-exchange-more-than-200000-worth-of-prizes-and-2-samsung-galaxy-s5-to-be-won', '', '', '2015-04-01 18:22:06', '2015-04-01 10:22:06', '', 0, 'http://en.tradehero.mobi/?p=1828', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1864, 6, '2015-05-06 18:03:27', '2015-05-06 10:03:27', '&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n\n<br>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nTradeHero was mentioned in <a href="https://www.facebook.com/CoconutsSingapore" data-gt="{&quot;entity_id&quot;:&quot;299002270220935&quot;,&quot;entity_path&quot;:&quot;/ajax/pagelet/generic.php:PhotoViewerInitPagelet&quot;}" data-hovercard="/ajax/hovercard/page.php?id=299002270220935&amp;extragetparams=%7B%22directed_target_id%22%3A0%7D">Coconuts Singapore</a> for our feature on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/techinasia" data-gt="{&quot;entity_id&quot;:&quot;175755689129519&quot;,&quot;entity_path&quot;:&quot;/ajax/pagelet/generic.php:PhotoViewerInitPagelet&quot;}" data-hovercard="/ajax/hovercard/page.php?id=175755689129519&amp;extragetparams=%7B%22directed_target_id%22%3A0%7D">Tech in Asia</a> Singapore 2015. You can read the article here: <a href="http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2F1AE6BQR&amp;h=hAQE6FVXU&amp;enc=AZNQ89Wn87Ueh_T5dsZgSCt-fU_D2R2cUtJ0eCQ3pNfH0f_H-9hw1fUDDpBM4WqtGT0HhnWMVDuHJlSEuD4mxbZTEqydxV-NGkeKPRNkqiichrrKXSSaC_5IDqIRvaHq1lbetaQRO4bTBC0QXzeLFAc-&amp;s=1" target="_blank" rel="nofollow nofollow">http://bit.ly/1AE6BQR</a>\n<br>\n<br>\nOur CEO and co-founder, Dinesh Bhatia shared how TradeHero became the #1 Finance app in 91 countries. Were you there to hear our success story?<br><br>\n<blockquote>Can you hear the clacking of keyboards yet?\n<br><br>\nFor two days and nights, Tech in Asia Singapore 2015 brings togethers the region''s tech industry movers and shakers as well as young innovators for a series of talks, workshops, speed-dating, games, competitions and pub crawls.\n<br><br>\nTech in Asia features speakers like SurveyMonkey''s Eli Schwartz who will share tips on how to use date to drive business, and Twitter''s Emily Huo for a keynote address on how startups can use Twitter to their advantage. They are just two of over 50 speakers in the lineup.\n<br><br>\nLook out for Singapore success stories like Dinesh Bhatia of Tradehero (named number one finance app in 81 countries) and Anthony Tan of GrabTaxi (who hasn''t booked a cab with them).\n<br><br>\nThere''s also a talk on space tech and why it''s so exciting by Nobu Okada, the founder of AstroScale, a startup that aims to remove killer litter from space (they''ve already raised $7.7-million, so they might be on to something).\n<br><br>\nNighttime will be as hectic as nighttime with opportunities to schmooze and booze with fellow delegates at sponsored night crawl events.\n<br><br>\n<em><a href="http://events.techinasia.com/sg2015/" target="_blank">Coconuts Singapore is a media partner with Tech in Asia Singapore 2015</a>, May 6 &amp; 7, Suntec Singapore Convention and Exhibition Centre.</em></blockquote>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<br><br>\n<a href="http://devtradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/11212613_795600930517262_1144965255617913735_o.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-1866 aligncenter" src="http://devtradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/11212613_795600930517262_1144965255617913735_o.jpg" alt="TradeHero CEO Dinesh Bhatia In Tech In Asia Singapore 2" width="501" height="375" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'TradeHero CEO, Dinesh Bhatia featured in Tech In Asia Singapore 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tradehero-ceo-dinesh-bhatia-featured-in-tech-in-asia-singapore-2015', '', '', '2015-05-06 18:03:27', '2015-05-06 10:03:27', '', 0, 'http://en.tradehero.mobi/?p=1864', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1873, 6, '2015-05-04 18:10:06', '2015-05-04 10:10:06', 'Have you always wanted to learn about Forex trading but have no idea where to start?\nLog in to TradeHero now and join the first ever Forex trading competition sponsored by OANDA.\n<br><br>\nThe OANDA FX Challenge starts today with US$15,000 worth of cash prizes to be won!\nComplete a new Trade Quest every month to qualify for a chance to win a Samsung Galaxy A5 in our monthly lucky draw.\n<br><br>\nNot familiar with FX trading? Fret not! You can learn all about FX by watching the educational videos directly in the TradeHero app.\n<br><br>\nCompetition runs from 4th May 2015 until 26 July 2015. See you at the top!\n<br><br>\nClick <a href="http://en.tradehero.mobi/oanda-fx-challenge">here</a> to find out more about OANDA FX CHALLENGE 2015', 'OANDA FX Challenge', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oanda-fx-challenge', '', '', '2015-05-04 18:10:06', '2015-05-04 10:10:06', '', 0, 'http://en.tradehero.mobi/?p=1873', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1881, 6, '2015-05-22 18:29:03', '2015-05-22 10:29:03', 'Our CEO, Dinesh Bhatia has been named by Fast Company Magazine as one of the 100 Most Creative People in Business 2015! Read all about it here in <a href="http://www.thetechrevolutionist.com/2015/05/singaporean-entrepreneur-named-among.html">The Tech Revolutionist</a>!<br><br>\n\n<a href="http://devtradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Dinesh.jpg"><img src="http://devtradehero.mobi/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Dinesh.jpg" alt="Dinesh Bhatia" width="500" height="500" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1625" /></a>\n\n<blockquote>Singapore’s very own <strong>Dinesh Bhatia, CEO of TradeHero</strong>, has been <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3043928/most-creative-people-2015/dinesh-bhatia">named</a> by Fast Company Magazine one of its “<strong>100 Most Creative People in Business 2015,” </strong>for<strong> teaching aspiring investors how to make the leap</strong>, making financial investment accessible to all.<strong> </strong>TradeHero, developed in Singapore in 2012, is now the <strong>#1 finance app in 91 countries</strong>, and in the <strong>top 10 in 127 countries</strong>, with <strong>over 3.6 million users</strong>.\n<br><br>\n\nDinesh is the only person from Singapore, and to our knowledge, ASEAN, to have made the 2015 list. He is in prestigious company. Previous winners include philanthropist <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018926/most-creative-people-2009/41-melinda-gates">Melinda Gates</a>, entrepreneur <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018422/most-creative-people-2011/16-elon-musk">Elon Musk</a>, TV personality <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018418/most-creative-people-2011/12-oprah-winfrey">Oprah Winfrey</a>, music producer <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018725/most-creative-people-2010/11-jay-z">Jay-Z</a>, musicians <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018785/most-creative-people-2010/70-jay-chou">Jay Chou</a>, <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018715/most-creative-people-2010/1-lady-gaga">Lady Gaga</a>, and <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/person/jared-leto">Jared Leto</a>, comedians <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018414/most-creative-people-2011/8-conan-obrien">Conan O’Brien</a>, <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3029462/most-creative-people-2014/jerry-seinfeld">Jerry Seinfeld</a>and <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018271/most-creative-people-2012/87-aziz-ansari">Aziz Ansari</a>, NBA star and entrepreneur <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/section/most-creative-people-2012">Shaquille O’Neal</a>, author <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018923/most-creative-people-2009/38-neil-gaiman">Neil Gaiman</a>, movie directors <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018723/most-creative-people-2010/9-james-cameron">James Cameron</a>, <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018885/most-creative-people-2009/1-jj-abrams">JJ Abrams</a> and <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018213/most-creative-people-2012/28-wes-anderson">Wes Anderson</a>, fashion designers <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018760/most-creative-people-2010/45-tom-ford">Tom Ford</a>, <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018947/most-creative-people-2009/57-marc-jacobs">Marc Jacobs</a> and <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/3018957/most-creative-people-2009/66-stella-mccartney">Stella McCartney</a>.\n<br><br>\nThe ‘100 Most Creative People in Business’ recognizes individuals from around the world whose creativity has the potential to reshape the business landscape. It looks around the world and across industries such as technology, science, entertainment, medicine and social media.\n<br><br>\n\nEach year, Fast Company Magazine’s editors create an all-new list of 100, chosen according to a proprietary methodology (honorees can''t repeat and anyone previously profiled in the print magazine is excluded). The resulting group represents highly accomplished, dynamic individuals whose work and ideas are driving the world forward.\n<br><br>\n\n<em>"Our goal is to discover and highlight the people around the world who are not just thinking differently, but also putting their ideas into action to create new opportunities, redefine the rules of modern business, and drive change within their own industries and beyond. In today''s rapidly evolving world, it''s creative and innovative leaders like these 100 who will continue to move the needle and inspire us all."  </em><strong>Fast Company editor Robert Safian</strong>\n<br><br>\n\n<em>Fast Company''s </em><strong>Most Creative People in Business </strong>issue (June 2015) is available online at <a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/section/most-creative-people-2015">http://www.fastcompany.com/section/most-creative-people-2015</a> as well as in app form via iTunes, and on newsstands beginning May 18.</blockquote><br><br>\n', 'TradeHero CEO, Dinesh Bhatia named 100 Most Creative People in Business 2015!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tradehero-ceo-dinesh-bhatia-named-100-most-creative-people-in-business-2015', '', '', '2015-05-22 18:29:03', '2015-05-22 10:29:03', '', 0, 'http://en.tradehero.mobi/?p=1881', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1886, 6, '2015-05-24 01:11:18', '2015-05-23 17:11:18', 'TradeHero was mentioned by CB Insights as one of the Fin Tech Startups that target the millenial demographics. Read the full article <a href="https://www.cbinsights.com/blog/fin-tech-startups-millennials/">here</a>\n<br><br>\n<blockquote>Fin Tech startups targeting the millennial demographic have raised over $2.29B across 126 deals. They range from ''robo-advisors'' offering low-cost alternatives to brokerages to lending firms innovating in credit risk to stock-picking and automated savings apps.\n<br><br>\nSpanning a cohort born between 1980 to 2000, millennials broadly make up one of the largest generations in history (bigger than the baby boom generation). Millennials are also investing, lending and sharing money much differently than their parents, and they are assisted by a growing set of tech-driven tools to do so.\n<br><br>\nThe changing ways in how millennials manage their money is top of mind for many of the largest financial institutions in the world. In February, Goldman Sachs released an <a href="http://www.goldmansachs.com/our-thinking/outlook/millennials/">infographic</a> on how millennial habits in health, marriage, housing and more are impacting the economy.\n<br><br>\nNow, a host of Fin Tech startups, and the investors backing them, are banking on millennials as a key demographic for their success. Fin Tech startups prominent in the millennial demographic range from ‘robo-advisors’ offering low-cost alternatives to brokerages to lending firms innovating in credit risk to stock-picking and automated savings apps.\n<br><br>\nMany of the Fin Tech startups are leveraging existing technologies already popular among young adults such as social networks and mobile messaging. Project crowdfunding sites GoFundMe and Andreessen Horowitz-backed <a href="http://cbinsights.com/company/tilt">Tilt</a>, for example, mirror or take advantage of social networks and are largely popular among college audiences. Google Ventures and General Catalyst-backed <a href="http://cbinsights.com/company/hello-digit">HelloDigit</a> transfers money directly via text message.\n<br><br>\nThe graphic below breaks down the set of Fin Tech companies appealing to the millennial generation including <a href="http://cbinsights.com/company/robinhood">Robinhood</a>, <a href="http://cbinsights.com/company/acorns-grow">Acorns</a>, <a href="http://cbinsights.com/company/wealthfront">Wealthfront</a>, <a href="http://cbinsights.com/company/earnest">Earnest</a> and more. In aggregate, millennial Fin Tech startups below have raised over $2.29B across 126 deals. Click the graphic to expand.</blockquote>\n&nbsp;\n\n<br><br>', 'TradeHero, One of The Fin Tech Startups Targeting Millennials', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tradehero-one-of-the-fin-tech-startups-targeting-millennials', '', '', '2015-05-24 01:11:18', '2015-05-23 17:11:18', '', 0, 'http://en.tradehero.mobi/?p=1886', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1890, 6, '2015-05-28 01:30:39', '2015-05-27 17:30:39', 'Read the article written by Digital News Asia <a href="https://www.digitalnewsasia.com/startups/tradehero-in-pacts-with-sgx-macquarie-securities-thailand">here</a>. TradeHero is also running a competition with SGX for our users called <a href="http://en.tradehero.mobi/sgxstockwhiz2015">SGX StockWhiz 2015 </a>where users can win prizes worth up to S$200,000.\n\n<br><br>\n<blockquote>SINGAPORE startup MyHero Ltd, the company behind financial learning and stock market simulation app <a href="http://en.tradehero.mobi/" target="_blank">TradeHero</a>, said it has partnered with the Singapore Exchange (SGX) to launch the SGX StockWhiz 2015 contest.\n<br><br>\nThis follows an agreement with Macquarie Securities Thailand (Macquarie) for DW Hero, a virtual derivative warrants (DW) trading contest.\n<br><br>\nThe partnerships would bring financial education, and make financial investments more accessible, to first-time investors, MyHero said in a statement.\n<br><br>\n<img class=" aligncenter" src="https://www.digitalnewsasia.com/sites/default/files/images/digital%20economy/Dinesh%20Bhatia%2C%20TradeHero.jpg" alt="" width="315" height="355" />\n<br>\n“Almost three million users on TradeHero’s free-to-download app are millennials, accounting for nearly 80% of its user base,” said MyHero chief executive officer and cofounder Dinesh Bhatia <strong><em>(pic)</em></strong>.\n<br><br>\n“In an era where first-time investors are acquiring financial literacy through gamified apps, TradeHero is playing a leading role in driving financial education.\n<br><br>\n“SGX and Macquarie have been quick to see this trend, particularly among millennials. Together, we aim to make learning fun, engaging and comprehensive, in turn cultivating a culture of investment among young investors,” he added.\n<br><br>\nA 2014 survey from Bankrate.com found that millennials (those born between 1980 and 2000) prefer cash three times as much as stocks for long-term investments, MyHero said.\n<br><br>\nThe same study also pointed out that while the S&amp;P 500 has gained 17% in the past year, most cash investments yielded less than 1%. Last year, Capital One ShareBuilder concluded that 93% of millennials lack knowledge on how to invest, making them less confident to do so.\n<br><br>\nWith SGX, TradeHero launched StockWhiz 2015, a risk-free way to learn about investing in the stock market.\n<br><br>\nStockwhiz 2015 is free-to-join and follows the success of StockWhiz 2014 which saw over 15,000 participants.\n<br><br>\nThis year, participants can ‘invest’ in more than 400 Stocks, Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITS) and Exchange Traded Funds (ETFs) listed on SGX, in real time.\n<br><br>\nThe overall winner, to be announced after the competition closes on June 30, will get S$3,000 (US$2,252) cash. Top performers will also get to keep their returns in real trading commission credits, sponsored by OCBC Securities, and stand to win over S$200,000 (more than US$150,000) in prizes.\n<br><br>\nTradeHero and SGX are also co-developing a series of educational video tutorials, covering a variety of topics, including the basics of trading and investing, riding big market cycles, and stock valuation.\n<br><br>\nAvailable as in-app ‘mobisodes’ on TradeHero as well as on the <a href="http://www.sgx.com/academy" target="_blank">SGX Academy website</a>, these videos will soon find use among various tertiary institutions to educate students and to promote financial literacy, MyHero said.\n<br><br>\nOver 90,000 people attended events and education programmes driven by SGX Academy and its partners in 2014, it added.\n<br><br>\nWith Macquarie, TradeHero launched DW Hero, a simulation game that allows investors to trade virtual derivative warrants (DWs).\n<br><br>\nUsing real time data from the Stock Exchange of Thailand (SET), DW Hero gives investors a real-time experience of trading DW without using actual money. DW Hero saw over 15,600 participants, with the top five winners generating over 100% returns, MyHero claimed.\n<br><br>\nIt also said that TradeHero is now the No 1 finance app in 91 countries, and in the top 10 in 127 countries, with over 3.6 million users.\n<br><br>\nIn September 2013, <a href="https://www.digitalnewsasia.com/sizzle-fizzle/singapores-tradehero-secures-usd10mil-series-a-funding" target="_blank">MyHero raised US$10 million</a> in Series A fundraising from Kleiner Perkins Caufield Byers'' China fund (KPCB China) and China-based IPV Capital. These investments helped TradeHero launch its product in Mainland China.\n<br><br>\nIn March 2015, <a href="https://www.digitalnewsasia.com/startups/tradehero-links-with-oanda-trading-forex-is-game-on" target="_blank">TradeHero linked platforms with Oanda</a>, an online foreign exchange broker and services proivder, to bring virtual currency and precious metals trading to TradeHero.\n\n&nbsp;</blockquote><br><br>', 'TradeHero in pacts with SGX, Macquarie Securities Thailand', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tradehero-in-pacts-with-sgx-macquarie-securities-thailand', '', '', '2015-05-28 01:30:39', '2015-05-27 17:30:39', '', 0, 'http://en.tradehero.mobi/?p=1890', 0, 'post', '', 0);
